WEBVTT

00:12:59.442 --> 00:13:02.577
SRB: It was known as
the British Airways Christmas Bonus.

00:13:02.601 --> 00:13:04.880
(Laughter)

00:13:04.904 --> 00:13:06.720
(Music)

00:13:06.744 --> 00:13:10.410
AG: In any rivalry, there are
opportunities to compete and to cooperate.

00:13:10.434 --> 00:13:13.499
There's a whole science showing
that you can do both effectively,

00:13:13.523 --> 00:13:15.720
but the order in which
you do them matters.

00:13:15.744 --> 00:13:18.268
You can see this in one
of my favorite experiments.

00:13:18.292 --> 00:13:19.988
Imagine you're playing a video game

00:13:20.012 --> 00:13:21.676
where you get to win cash prizes

00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:24.577
for attacking enemies
and defending your territory.

00:13:24.601 --> 00:13:26.990
In one round, the other players
are your teammates.

00:13:27.014 --> 00:13:28.901
In the other, they're your competitors.

00:13:29.378 --> 00:13:31.863
Researchers actually tried this
a few years ago,